Taiwan Stocks: Acer, Nanya Tech, Pegatron, Phison Electronics

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-07-21T05:51:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/taiwan-stocks-nanya-technology-phison-taiwan-semiconductor.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei  The Taiex Index rose 10.97 points, or 0.1 percent, to
8,717.14.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT) advanced 3.6 percent to NT$41.35, the
biggest advance since June 29, after the company said it will
announce details of an acquisition at a briefing at 2 p.m. in
Taipei. Acer plans to make an acquisition using cash and shares,
the Taiwan stock exchange said in a statement today, without
giving details. Henry Wang, a spokesman at Acer, declined to
comment.  Nanya Technology Corp. (2408)  (2408 TT) sank 5.9 percent to
NT$6.23, slumping for a fourth day to a record low. Taiwan’s
second-largest memory-chip maker said on July 19 its second-
quarter loss widened to NT$7.9 billion ($274 million) from a
loss of NT$1.1 billion a year earlier.  Pegatron Corp. (4938)  (4938 TT) advanced 2.7 percent to NT$34.80
after Apple Daily News reported the company got Apple Inc.’s
orders to assemble the next-generation iPhone and iPad, without
saying where it got the information. Pegatron Chief Financial
Officer Charles Lin wasn’t immediately available for comment at
his office.  Phison Electronics Corp. (8299)  (8299 TT) dropped 1.4 percent to
NT$140. The maker of NAND flash chips used to store data in
digital cameras, portable music players and mobile phones was
rated “reduce” in new coverage at Nomura Holdings Inc. The
brokerage has a share-price estimate of NT$105.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
